    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PSO140-61 - PRECAUTIONS -
        CLEANLINESS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CLEANLINESS</title>
        <para>Transmissions should be steam cleaned prior to disassembly. Seal all openings before steam cleaning to
            prevent entry of dirt and water which can damage serviceable parts.
        </para>
        <para>Dirt is abrasive and will cause premature wear of bearings and other parts. We suggest that mechanics have
            a small wash tank to clean parts just prior to reassembly.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
